00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.220
How To Prepare For Your
Upcoming Open House

00:00:02.862 --> 00:00:06.562
An open house is a great way to
market your home and give potential

00:00:06.562 --> 00:00:09.892
buyers the opportunity to walk
through the property in person.

00:00:10.372 --> 00:00:14.862
A licensed agent will be on site
to host the open house and handle

00:00:14.942 --> 00:00:16.312
everything during the event.

00:00:17.337 --> 00:00:20.857
To ensure the open house goes
smoothly, there are a few important

00:00:20.857 --> 00:00:22.227
things to do ahead of time.

00:00:23.537 --> 00:00:26.867
First, sellers should not be
present during the open house.

00:00:27.187 --> 00:00:29.557
This allows buyers to feel
comfortable walking through the

00:00:29.557 --> 00:00:31.917
home and asking questions freely.

00:00:33.224 --> 00:00:34.095
One Week Before

00:00:34.624 --> 00:00:37.934
About a week before the open house,
do a depersonalization check.

00:00:38.115 --> 00:00:42.664
Put away personal photos, heirlooms,
valuables, and sensitive personal items.

00:00:43.512 --> 00:00:46.972
Plan to deep clean the home and
create a simple routine to keep it

00:00:47.012 --> 00:00:49.232
tidy leading up to the open house.

00:00:50.222 --> 00:00:54.502
This is also a good time to tend to
the yard by mowing, trimming bushes,

00:00:54.502 --> 00:00:58.532
and clearing walkways so the exterior
makes a strong first impression.

00:00:59.299 --> 00:01:00.150
One Day Before

00:01:00.687 --> 00:01:04.047
The day before the open house, vacuum,
mop, and dust throughout the home.

00:01:04.707 --> 00:01:07.087
Focus on kitchens, bathrooms, and floors.

00:01:07.612 --> 00:01:09.932
Do a quick sniff test and
take care of any odors.

00:01:10.472 --> 00:01:14.022
Clean pet areas thoroughly and
air out the home if needed.

00:01:14.887 --> 00:01:15.947
A Few Hours Before

00:01:16.462 --> 00:01:19.552
A few hours before the open
house, open windows if the weather

00:01:19.552 --> 00:01:21.202
allows to bring in fresh air.

00:01:23.022 --> 00:01:25.652
Turn on all lights so the home
feels bright and welcoming.

00:01:26.337 --> 00:01:29.237
Pets should be removed from
the home during the open house.

00:01:29.627 --> 00:01:32.867
This is important for both
buyer comfort and safety.

00:01:33.937 --> 00:01:37.457
Secure personal documents, mail,
and any sensitive information.

00:01:38.047 --> 00:01:40.337
Take out the trash and
hide bins out of sight.

00:01:41.075 --> 00:01:45.055
Put away everyday clutter such as
shoes, jackets, and countertop items.

00:01:45.714 --> 00:01:49.234
Do one final walkthrough of each room
to make sure everything is clean,

00:01:49.325 --> 00:01:51.125
orderly, and ready for visitors.

00:01:51.812 --> 00:01:56.502
Taking these steps helps create a positive
experience for buyers and allows the open

00:01:56.502 --> 00:01:58.882
house to showcase your home at its best.

